# cached OAuth tokens (Calendar MCP / Calendar API):
token*.json

# Pocket CFO runtime artifacts (never commit real financial data or eval traces).
# NOTE: .gitignore has NO inline comments — keep each comment on its own line.
# The local redacted ledger and learned corrections are user data, not source:
app/data/ledger.json
app/data/corrections.json
# agents-cli eval traces + grade results:
artifacts/
# Google Calendar API credentials (OAuth client secret + the token it produces).
# Real secrets — download the client secret yourself, never commit either file:
app/data/calendar_client_secret.json
app/data/calendar_token.json
# Ephemeral PKCE state between the two-step manual OAuth flow (short-lived):
app/data/.calendar_oauth_state.json
# Cached id of the dedicated "Pocket CFO Demo" calendar (per-account, not a secret,
# but environment-specific state -- not source):
app/data/calendar_demo_id.json
# ...but DO track the synthetic sample docs used for demos/tests:
!app/data/seed/
